Electronic Arts is offering Dead Space for free to PC gamers. Gamers can add the game to their library permanently by redeeming it on the Origin Store while the giveaway is active. Dead Space is the latest game to be offered for free in Originâ€™s On the House programme, which aims to drive adoption of the platform. Previous On the House titles include Battlefield 3, Dragon Age: Origins, and Command & Conquer: Red Alert 2. EA said Dead Space was only available for free for a limited time, but did not state when the promotion would expire.